SP.P:
Well at thy entreaty I will doe it. Giue me my Cloake


there, buy a linck and meet me at the Counter in Woodstreete;
busse me Moll.

I but when light Wiues make heauy hus∣bands,
let these husbands play mad Hamlet; and crie reuenge,
come, and  do so.

Hold, Ile speake in a small voice
like one of the women; here's a friend: are you vp? rize, rize;
stir, stirre.
